  Locus:
    Page: 176
    Verse: 2
Tags:
  - Friendship
---
Taking friendship for granted is one of the surest ways of ending them.
Unless nourished, they tend to wither and die. Unless we earnestly desire
its continuance we should never start a friendship any more than we would a
love affair.
